HEADWORD: Hexapla
<hw>Hex"a*pla</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>Etym.
<pos>pl.</pos>, but syntactically <pos>sing.</pos></ety> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/, fr. <?/, contr. <?/, sixfold.]</ety> <def>A collection of the
Holy Scriptures in six languages or six versions in parallel columns;
particularly, the edition of the Old Testament published by Origen, in
the 3d century.</def>⟦br⟧
